00:15:15.267 --> 00:15:18.800
But now raise your hand
if you successfully

00:15:18.800 --> 00:15:23.290
guessed that the storefront
would be ranked last.

00:15:23.290 --> 00:15:25.030
Not that many of you, like me.

00:15:25.030 --> 00:15:26.410
I was a bit surprised, too.

00:15:26.410 --> 00:15:28.162
Now raise your hand
if you just thought

00:15:28.162 --> 00:15:30.370
this whole thing was contrived
to make the Play Store

00:15:30.370 --> 00:15:30.870
look good.

00:15:30.870 --> 00:15:32.940
[LAUGHTER]

00:15:32.940 --> 00:15:33.440
All right.

00:15:33.440 --> 00:15:36.020
So there's at least some
cynics in the audience,

00:15:36.020 --> 00:15:38.750
and I appreciate that.

00:15:38.750 --> 00:15:41.390
So when I saw these results, I
wondered, how is this possible?

00:15:41.390 --> 00:15:43.265
With the billions of
people that are visiting

00:15:43.265 --> 00:15:48.440
the store and the fact that
all discovery roads end in one

00:15:48.440 --> 00:15:51.430
app store and the other, where
is this disconnect coming from?

00:15:51.430 --> 00:15:54.350
Do developers believe that most
users have made up their mind

00:15:54.350 --> 00:15:56.828
before they come to the store?

00:15:56.828 --> 00:15:58.120
I was wondering the same thing.

00:15:58.120 --> 00:15:59.410
Well, I did some digging.

00:15:59.410 --> 00:16:01.630
And in fact, a majority
of store sessions

00:16:01.630 --> 00:16:03.670
are discovery-focused,
with people

00:16:03.670 --> 00:16:05.590
searching for things
like free games

00:16:05.590 --> 00:16:08.140
or scrolling through
the home page.

00:16:08.140 --> 00:16:10.780
So my takeaway was
that, we, as Play,

00:16:10.780 --> 00:16:14.260
have a tremendous opportunity
to improve the effectiveness

00:16:14.260 --> 00:16:15.400
of game discovery.

00:16:15.400 --> 00:16:20.130
And here is how we think
about that opportunity.

00:16:20.130 --> 00:16:22.190
So for years, game
discovery started

00:16:22.190 --> 00:16:24.910
with the tried and
trusted game icon--

00:16:24.910 --> 00:16:27.170
lots of icons, all
of the game icons.

00:16:27.170 --> 00:16:29.300
And we know that you
put a lot of effort

00:16:29.300 --> 00:16:31.920
into carefully
crafting these things.

00:16:31.920 --> 00:16:35.180
But there are physical limits
to how much information these

00:16:35.180 --> 00:16:37.250
could possibly convey to users.

00:16:37.250 --> 00:16:41.690
The game icon is really
just a narrow, keyhole-view

00:16:41.690 --> 00:16:44.110
into the store listing.

00:16:44.110 --> 00:16:46.610
And the store listing has a lot
more information-- there are

00:16:46.610 --> 00:16:48.500
videos, there are screenshots.

00:16:48.500 --> 00:16:51.500
But the store listing is
still just another slightly,

00:16:51.500 --> 00:16:54.440
less narrow keyhole-view
into the layer

00:16:54.440 --> 00:16:57.110
below the actual game.

00:16:57.110 --> 00:17:00.740
And each layer, sure, provides
more information than the last.

00:17:00.740 --> 00:17:03.200
But playing the game is
really the first time

00:17:03.200 --> 00:17:05.930
the user can tell if they
found a match for what

00:17:05.930 --> 00:17:07.410
they're looking for.

00:17:07.410 --> 00:17:09.740
So we asked
ourselves, how can we

00:17:09.740 --> 00:17:12.770
elevate what's inside
the game-- the soul

00:17:12.770 --> 00:17:15.569
or essence of the game-- to
the front line of discovery?

00:17:15.569 --> 00:17:19.160
How do we move things from this
bottom layer up to the top,

00:17:19.160 --> 00:17:22.170
further and further up?

00:17:22.170 --> 00:17:24.140
And over the last few
years, we've, in fact,

00:17:24.140 --> 00:17:25.807
been making progress
towards this goal--

00:17:25.807 --> 00:17:27.680
some of this Tian
covered earlier--

00:17:27.680 --> 00:17:31.160
moving content like
trailers and screenshots

00:17:31.160 --> 00:17:34.070
from the store listing
to the top layer.

00:17:34.070 --> 00:17:36.650
We recently expanded to
auto-playing elements

00:17:36.650 --> 00:17:38.595
like this, which Tian
mentioned earlier.

00:17:38.595 --> 00:17:40.362
And there's also a
ton of activity inside

00:17:40.362 --> 00:17:42.320
of games in that bottom
layer, the stuff that's

00:17:42.320 --> 00:17:45.020
happening inside the game--
daily events, competitions

00:17:45.020 --> 00:17:46.070
and promotions.

00:17:46.070 --> 00:17:48.560
And that's where
live events come in

00:17:48.560 --> 00:17:50.580
and why we have the Events tab.

00:17:50.580 --> 00:17:53.360
And we believe the next step
in the store's evolution

00:17:53.360 --> 00:17:56.870
is to bring more of the
essence or soul of the game up

00:17:56.870 --> 00:17:58.370
to that top layer.

00:17:58.370 --> 00:18:02.640
And Google Play Instant plays
an important role in this area.

00:18:02.640 --> 00:18:04.370
So this next section
is going to provide

00:18:04.370 --> 00:18:06.980
an update on how the
product has matured

00:18:06.980 --> 00:18:09.680
since we talked about it and
announced it at GDC last year.

00:18:13.697 --> 00:18:15.530
So as a quick refresher,
Google Play Instant

00:18:15.530 --> 00:18:18.740
enables users to start games
instantly with a single tap,

00:18:18.740 --> 00:18:21.650
to try the game without
installing or uninstalling,

00:18:21.650 --> 00:18:24.170
and gives you the ability to
launch games from anywhere,

00:18:24.170 --> 00:18:28.200
all over the store, and
Play's properties beyond that.

00:18:28.200 --> 00:18:31.620
And since GDC last
year, developer adoption

00:18:31.620 --> 00:18:33.150
has been booming.

00:18:33.150 --> 00:18:36.450
Over the last six months,
we've seen 3x growth

00:18:36.450 --> 00:18:39.610
in instant games, and sessions
have grown even further.

00:18:39.610 --> 00:18:41.820
So we asked ourselves,
with that success,

00:18:41.820 --> 00:18:43.710
can we elevate
instant games further?

00:18:43.710 --> 00:18:45.535
What else can we do
with this format?

00:18:45.535 --> 00:18:47.160
Could we shift instant
games from being

00:18:47.160 --> 00:18:50.340
just part of the existing
discovery experience to being

00:18:50.340 --> 00:18:54.870
"the" discovery experience?

00:18:54.870 --> 00:18:57.570
Well, the Play
Games App Playlists

00:18:57.570 --> 00:19:00.000
are the first real
attempt to do this.

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:02.610
Imagine in the future
being able to click "Play

00:19:02.610 --> 00:19:05.552
All" on the new and updated
section on the store

00:19:05.552 --> 00:19:07.260
and having an experience
like this, where

00:19:07.260 --> 00:19:11.940
you can go from demo to demo to
demo until you found something

00:19:11.940 --> 00:19:14.066
you love to play.

00:19:14.066 --> 00:19:18.110
Think about how different
that experience would be when

00:19:18.110 --> 00:19:19.410
you are looking for a game.

00:19:19.410 --> 00:19:20.940
And the Play Games
app and the store

00:19:20.940 --> 00:19:23.660
are going to continue to invest
and iterate and experiment

00:19:23.660 --> 00:19:25.692
with concepts like this.

00:19:25.692 --> 00:19:27.150
And our success
has also emboldened

00:19:27.150 --> 00:19:33.270
us to elevate instant games from
the store listing to the higher

00:19:33.270 --> 00:19:38.540
layers here on the home page,
like in this ads example, one

00:19:38.540 --> 00:19:41.150
of the new "Try Now" treatments
that we're testing out.

00:19:41.150 --> 00:19:44.390
So expect to see more "Try
Now" buttons on the home page

00:19:44.390 --> 00:19:45.832
in the near future.

00:19:45.832 --> 00:19:47.540
And all these new
experiences were really

00:19:47.540 --> 00:19:49.550
made possible because of
the incredible support

00:19:49.550 --> 00:19:51.760
of our partners who
build instant games.

00:19:51.760 --> 00:19:53.930
So the question is, why
were they building them?

00:19:53.930 --> 00:19:55.920
What's behind this growth?

00:19:55.920 --> 00:19:57.800
So there are three
driving forces.

00:19:57.800 --> 00:20:00.920
The first, Google Play Instant
is delivering business impact

00:20:00.920 --> 00:20:03.860
to you, the game developer.

00:20:03.860 --> 00:20:06.440
Second, we've made
it easier and faster

00:20:06.440 --> 00:20:08.300
for you to build instant games.

00:20:08.300 --> 00:20:11.960
And lastly, we've cultivated
an ecosystem of implementation

00:20:11.960 --> 00:20:16.790
and technology partners that can
help you build instant games.

00:20:16.790 --> 00:20:18.970
So diving into business
uplift, the key thing

00:20:18.970 --> 00:20:21.970
I want you to take away is
that Google Play Instant

00:20:21.970 --> 00:20:25.840
can work for any game,
any of your games.

00:20:25.840 --> 00:20:29.200
And here's a sample of
recent successful games

00:20:29.200 --> 00:20:30.760
to help illustrate
a few key points.

00:20:30.760 --> 00:20:33.880
So number one, they've
all achieved improvements

00:20:33.880 --> 00:20:36.160
for the developer
in terms of number

00:20:36.160 --> 00:20:37.900
of users that install the game.

00:20:37.900 --> 00:20:43.020
That's a big, important thing
to emphasize-- from 6% to 26%.

00:20:43.020 --> 00:20:45.570
But in addition
to that, it's also

00:20:45.570 --> 00:20:48.510
important to emphasize
that success can be

00:20:48.510 --> 00:20:50.277
found in any category of game.

00:20:50.277 --> 00:20:52.110
So whether or not you're
building a strategy

00:20:52.110 --> 00:20:55.140
game, an arcade game,
or a casual game,

00:20:55.140 --> 00:20:57.980
you can find success.

00:20:57.980 --> 00:21:00.670
And second, irrespective of
how you monetize your game,

00:21:00.670 --> 00:21:02.560
Google Play Instant
can work for you.

00:21:02.560 --> 00:21:05.380
And that impact can be
particularly pronounced

00:21:05.380 --> 00:21:10.520
for premium games, as
this example illustrates.

00:21:10.520 --> 00:21:13.160
And lastly, you can
find success, regardless

00:21:13.160 --> 00:21:16.250
of how you have built
your instant game.

00:21:16.250 --> 00:21:19.760
So whether you prefer to use
HTML, like "Flip the Gun,"

00:21:19.760 --> 00:21:23.090
or Unity, like
"Rodeo Stampede" did,

00:21:23.090 --> 00:21:25.160
or a custom engine
or AppOnboard,

00:21:25.160 --> 00:21:26.697
you can be successful.

00:21:26.697 --> 00:21:28.280
And speaking of
developer tools, we've

00:21:28.280 --> 00:21:30.960
made major strides in this area.

00:21:30.960 --> 00:21:33.470
So in the lead up to GDC,
our early access partners

00:21:33.470 --> 00:21:36.420
were taking months to
build an instant game.

00:21:36.420 --> 00:21:38.270
And with our investment
in Unity and Cocos,

00:21:38.270 --> 00:21:42.200
we got it down to weeks,
then we got it down to days.

00:21:42.200 --> 00:21:45.020
But going forward, we
aspire to do two things--

00:21:45.020 --> 00:21:46.730
enable developers to
build instant games

00:21:46.730 --> 00:21:49.550
in a matter of hours, to
cut that down even more,

00:21:49.550 --> 00:21:51.240
and enable every
single one of you

00:21:51.240 --> 00:21:53.140
in the audience to
build an instant game.

00:21:53.140 --> 00:21:54.890
And for those of you
who may be skeptical,

00:21:54.890 --> 00:21:56.600
we have a video
demonstration that

00:21:56.600 --> 00:22:00.040
shows that this is possible
courtesy of AppOnboard.

00:22:03.070 --> 00:22:04.782
The demo was of their
new studio product

00:22:04.782 --> 00:22:07.240
that was announced last week
that takes a codeless approach

00:22:07.240 --> 00:22:08.590
to building instant games.

00:22:08.590 --> 00:22:11.660
And just a warning, the demo
runs at 18 times normal speed,

00:22:11.660 --> 00:22:15.560
so I will be talking quickly.

00:22:15.560 --> 00:22:16.400
All right.

00:22:16.400 --> 00:22:19.780
So you create a project.

00:22:19.780 --> 00:22:22.350
And after you've created
the video and audio assets,

00:22:22.350 --> 00:22:25.320
you can actually import
them into Studio,

00:22:25.320 --> 00:22:27.330
where you can drag and
drop them to build out

00:22:27.330 --> 00:22:28.410
your user experience.

00:22:28.410 --> 00:22:30.990
You can set up your transitions
and link them to gestures,

00:22:30.990 --> 00:22:32.550
like clicking and swiping.

00:22:32.550 --> 00:22:35.100
You can quickly preview
experience and iterate

00:22:35.100 --> 00:22:36.550
through that process.

00:22:36.550 --> 00:22:39.030
And as you can see in
this time lapse here,

00:22:39.030 --> 00:22:43.110
in under 10 minutes, you could
have your first iteration

00:22:43.110 --> 00:22:45.680
of an instant game.

00:22:45.680 --> 00:22:47.730
And this approach to
build instant games

00:22:47.730 --> 00:22:50.003
could unlock a whole
new range of use cases.

00:22:50.003 --> 00:22:52.170
Imagine in the future having
different instant games

00:22:52.170 --> 00:22:55.650
for every user segment,
for every content update,

00:22:55.650 --> 00:22:58.950
for every live
event or promotion.

00:22:58.950 --> 00:23:02.550
That's the future we
are building towards.

00:23:02.550 --> 00:23:04.750
And another important signal
of Instant's maturation

00:23:04.750 --> 00:23:07.990
is the implementation
partner ecosystem that's

00:23:07.990 --> 00:23:09.730
growing up around the product.

00:23:09.730 --> 00:23:13.810
And they help solve critical
problems in adoption for us.

00:23:13.810 --> 00:23:19.275
And they have been critical
to our success, as a result.

00:23:19.275 --> 00:23:21.650
So to learn more about these
partners and everything else

00:23:21.650 --> 00:23:26.330
I talked about today, check
out our GDC medium post here.

00:23:26.330 --> 00:23:28.460
And come to our session
at the Google booth

00:23:28.460 --> 00:23:31.670
this Wednesday, to learn how to
build instant games with Unity.

00:23:31.670 --> 00:23:33.890
And with that, I'll
hand things over to Kobi

00:23:33.890 --> 00:23:36.904
to talk about the power
of Play distribution.

