00:35:29.540 --> 00:35:31.330
and ANR rate.

00:35:31.330 --> 00:35:34.870
In the battery area we
have stuck wake locks

00:35:34.870 --> 00:35:36.280
and excessive wakeups.

00:35:40.755 --> 00:35:42.540
For each of these
core vitals, we

00:35:42.540 --> 00:35:43.830
have a bad behavior threshold.

00:35:43.830 --> 00:35:45.930
And the bad behavior
threshold enables

00:35:45.930 --> 00:35:47.430
you to be able to
know if you're one

00:35:47.430 --> 00:35:52.250
of the worst performing
games for that metric.

00:35:52.250 --> 00:35:55.760
For the other vitals metrics,
we want you to look at them

00:35:55.760 --> 00:35:58.605
and be able to see how you're
performing relative to others.

00:35:58.605 --> 00:36:01.370
And I'll talk to you
about that in a second.

00:36:01.370 --> 00:36:03.950
Some of the vitals
metrics we have right now,

00:36:03.950 --> 00:36:06.050
such as the rendering
metrics, just

00:36:06.050 --> 00:36:08.570
capture UI
toolkit-rendered frames,

00:36:08.570 --> 00:36:11.390
and so they don't
capture open GL.

00:36:11.390 --> 00:36:14.120
And so there are no
bad behavior thresholds

00:36:14.120 --> 00:36:17.600
for the rendering metrics or
the other non-core vitals.

00:36:17.600 --> 00:36:20.360
It's an area that we
are working to improve

00:36:20.360 --> 00:36:23.450
in terms of having more
insights for your games

00:36:23.450 --> 00:36:24.670
that are using open GL.

00:36:29.890 --> 00:36:32.340
One of the things that Google
Play is uniquely positioned

00:36:32.340 --> 00:36:35.500
to offer is benchmarking
across different games,

00:36:35.500 --> 00:36:39.550
because we have the data
across the platform.

00:36:39.550 --> 00:36:42.050
Right now we offer
category-level benchmarks.

00:36:42.050 --> 00:36:45.550
So for each vital metric, you
can go in and select which

00:36:45.550 --> 00:36:49.960
category of the Play Store that
you're in across all the games

00:36:49.960 --> 00:36:51.460
categories that we
currently support

00:36:51.460 --> 00:36:54.550
and see if you're doing worse
or better than the competitors

00:36:54.550 --> 00:36:55.650
in that market.

00:36:55.650 --> 00:36:58.060
And so you can see
then that games

00:36:58.060 --> 00:37:02.050
