about what we're doing.

00:41:07.270 --> 00:41:10.960
During this phase, we are
monitoring both ANR crash

00:41:10.960 --> 00:41:13.060
rates, which are the
issues that we have

00:41:13.060 --> 00:41:15.560
the most, most of the time.

00:41:15.560 --> 00:41:17.920
And these are being checked
constantly and proactively

00:41:17.920 --> 00:41:19.600
across the whole period.

00:41:19.600 --> 00:41:22.310
After that's done, we'll
go into live monitoring,

00:41:22.310 --> 00:41:24.530
which is business as
usual for most games.

00:41:24.530 --> 00:41:26.710
So there's not just
actually deployment,

00:41:26.710 --> 00:41:28.630
but it's where we shift--

00:41:28.630 --> 00:41:31.640
from a business perspective, we
shift to a much more proactive

00:41:31.640 --> 00:41:32.140
approach.

00:41:32.140 --> 00:41:34.140
So we're tracking the
deeper metrics in the game

00:41:34.140 --> 00:41:36.760
that we can't really
see during deployment.

00:41:36.760 --> 00:41:38.710
And from a technical
perspective,

00:41:38.710 --> 00:41:42.760
we go into a more reactive
side based largely on alarms.

00:41:42.760 --> 00:41:46.390
So using Crashlytics and
vitals to having alarms

00:41:46.390 --> 00:41:49.000
on all the stores and all
the games that we have.

00:41:49.000 --> 00:41:52.150
Because honestly, if you have
400 titles, checking all of

00:41:52.150 --> 00:41:55.680
them manually is
just not feasible.

00:41:55.680 --> 00:41:57.420
I want to share with
you a simple use

00:41:57.420 --> 00:41:59.120
case that I'm sure
several of you

00:41:59.120 --> 00:42:01.320
have gone through
across the years, which

00:42:01.320 --> 00:42:04.770
was one of our releases last
year on "Bid Wars," which

00:42:04.770 --> 00:42:07.590
is our current biggest title.

00:42:07.590 --> 00:42:10.260
So we were releasing a new
version, several updates,

00:42:10.260 --> 00:42:14.140
several partner
updates, and, of course,

00:42:14.140 --> 00:42:17.370
getting a lot of
technical fixes online.

00:42:17.370 --> 00:42:20.430
In this case, both our
technical and business teams

00:42:20.430 --> 00:42:24.060
