we were rolling out.

00:42:24.060 --> 00:42:25.770
So we got a spike on reviews.

00:42:25.770 --> 00:42:28.410
Our games usually have
relatively good reviews.

00:42:28.410 --> 00:42:30.510
So getting a spike saying
people couldn't access

00:42:30.510 --> 00:42:31.765
a game or the game
was crashing, there

00:42:31.765 --> 00:42:33.060
was definitely something wrong.

00:42:33.060 --> 00:42:35.640
And lo and behold, we
were also getting a spike

00:42:35.640 --> 00:42:37.980
on ANRs of the game.

00:42:37.980 --> 00:42:40.980
Investigating this was done
as soon as we were reaching

00:42:40.980 --> 00:42:42.810
20% rollout, so
we didn't actually

00:42:42.810 --> 00:42:44.670
reach the whole user base.

00:42:44.670 --> 00:42:47.070
And pretty much what
was done was just--

00:42:47.070 --> 00:42:49.350
it was on Android specifically,
so we were checking,

00:42:49.350 --> 00:42:52.470
we were seeing that we were
getting a lot of crashes

00:42:52.470 --> 00:42:54.570
on specific third-party SDK.

00:42:54.570 --> 00:42:55.500
How do you solve that?

00:42:55.500 --> 00:42:57.370
As everyone else does.

00:42:57.370 --> 00:43:02.220
So pull it out, stop rollout,
and actually remove that SDK.

00:43:02.220 --> 00:43:05.340
It was something that would take
a little bit longer to test.

00:43:05.340 --> 00:43:07.532
It's very important, though,
to notice that this is

00:43:07.532 --> 00:43:08.740
something very common, right?

00:43:08.740 --> 00:43:10.750
There's no secret sauce here.

00:43:10.750 --> 00:43:12.960
But I'm pretty sure all of
you have seen this before.

00:43:12.960 --> 00:43:15.660
And for us, being able to
catch this before it actually

00:43:15.660 --> 00:43:17.560
impacted our revenue,
so it actually impacted

00:43:17.560 --> 00:43:20.140
most of our users,
it's very important.

00:43:20.140 --> 00:43:24.910
And this is part of what we
learned across the years.

00:43:24.910 --> 00:43:27.000
So first, the tools
themselves don't

00:43:27.000 --> 00:43:28.390
have to be that complicated.

00:43:28.390 --> 00:43:31.560
So know that you don't have
to necessarily overshoot.

00:43:31.560 --> 00:43:35.520
You don't need a complicated,
technical analysis team

00:43:35.520 --> 00:43:36.990
to make it work.

00:43:36.990 --> 00:43:39.120
You can just have
tools that give you

00:43:39.120 --> 00:43:40.980
what you can react upon.

00:43:40.980 --> 00:43:43.828
Second, quality of the app.

00:43:43.828 --> 00:43:45.870
Differently, from what
you used to do in the past

00:43:45.870 --> 00:43:48.450
and from what most
people do, it's

00:43:48.450 --> 00:43:50.190
not about just a technical team.

00:43:50.190 --> 00:43:51.833
